@startuml
skinparam style strictuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
title US-04 Input Parameters:Encoder Constructors

actor Developer
participant "Encoder Constructors" as EC
participant "InputHandler" as IH
participant "Brain" as B
participant "InputField" as IFTS

Developer -> EC: pass encoder parameters\n(e.g., ScalarEncoderParameters, RDSEParameters)
EC --> Developer: configured encoder instances

Developer -> IH: input_data(input_source, required_columns)
activate IH
IH -> IH: _process_dataframe(df, required_columns)
opt required_columns provided
  IH -> IH: add missing columns
end
IH --> Developer: normalized dict[Any, list[Any]]
deactivate IH

Developer -> B: initialize Brain with configured components/params
activate B
B --> Developer: ready for step(inputs, learn)
deactivate B

B -> IFTS: initialize with provided encoder parameters
activate IFTS
IFTS --> B: encoder ready
deactivate IFTS

note over EC,B
Brain is the runtime entry point for encoder parameters.
Parameter tuning is also entered manually via constructor args dataclass.
end note
@enduml
